records.addlTxt:
01:45 PM Defendant Kyle R Orr in court, in custody, with attorney Angela Wang.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern, Jack Rieder, appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Cases called for plea and sentencing.
State places offer on the record. 
Court conducts plea colloquy.

In case 22CF461:
Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Count 1,  Court finds defendant guilty.
In case 22CM26:
Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Count 2,  Court finds defendant guilty.
Counts 1 & 3 are Dismissed and read in.
Case 21CT1668 is Dismissed and read in. 
State and Defense make sentencing recommendations.

Court orders the following:
In case 22CF461:
SENTENCE WITHHELD.

Term of Probation:  3 YEARS; 

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  Court does not object to transfer to Milwaukee County if accepted; 
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
*Not to use or possess any vaping or CBD products;
*Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
*Thinking for Change Class through Agent: 
*No contact with:  Walmart; 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done;
*No operation of a motor vehicle with a valid driver's license;

CONDITION TIME: 60 DAYS Straight-Time, STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  

RESTITUTION:  $559.71 to Walmart (Restitution to be paid before costs or fines);
COSTS:  Waived by the Court; 
DNA SAMPLE AND SURCHARGE:  $250
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
To be paid as a Condition of Probation.
**********************************************
In case 22CM26:
JAIL:  30 days (Credit - 30 days). TIME SERVED;

COSTS: Waived by the Court; 

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200;
Defendant to provide DNA sample, within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
To be paid as a Condition of Probation in 22CF461.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
Defendant may be returned to the appropriate facility forthwith.
